# Separator

A thin divider for visually separating content.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/separator
import ui/typography

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  html.div([attribute.class("flex flex-col gap-4 w-[320px]")], [
    typography.body([], [html.text("A horizontal separator splits stacks.")]),
    separator.root([], []),
    html.div([attribute.class("flex h-5 items-center gap-4 text-sm")], [
      html.span([], [html.text("Docs")]),
      separator.root([separator.vertical()], []),
      html.span([], [html.text("Source")]),
      separator.root([separator.vertical()], []),
      html.span([], [html.text("Issues")]),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## Installation

Install this element and its dependencies with the Drip CLI:

```sh
gleam run -m drip -- add separator
```

## Usage

```gleam
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import ui/separator

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  separator.root([], [])
}
```

## Examples

Set the rule's axis with the orientation attributes, or break the line with centered content.

### Horizontal

Pass the horizontal attribute to lay the rule across the parent's inline width. This is the default orientation.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/separator
import ui/typography

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  html.div([attribute.class("flex flex-col gap-3 w-[320px]")], [
    typography.body([], [html.text("Above the line.")]),
    separator.root([separator.horizontal()], []),
    typography.body([], [html.text("Below the line.")]),
  ])
}
```

### Vertical

Pass the vertical attribute to stretch the rule to the parent's block height.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/separator

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  html.div([attribute.class("flex h-5 items-center gap-4 text-sm")], [
    html.span([], [html.text("Inbox")]),
    separator.root([separator.vertical()], []),
    html.span([], [html.text("Drafts")]),
    separator.root([separator.vertical()], []),
    html.span([], [html.text("Sent")]),
  ])
}
```

### Content

Pass children to the separator to render centered content over the line.

```gleam
import lustre/attribute
import lustre/element.{type Element}
import lustre/element/html
import ui/button
import ui/separator

pub fn view() -> Element(message) {
  html.div([attribute.class("flex flex-col gap-3 w-[320px]")], [
    button.button([button.primary()], [html.text("Sign in with email")]),
    separator.root([], [html.text("or")]),
    button.button([button.outline()], [
      html.text("Continue with a single-use link"),
    ]),
  ])
}
```

## API Reference

### Orientation Attributes

Two orientation attributes, one per axis. Pass one into the root's attribute list.

| Attribute | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `separator.horizontal()` | Lays the rule along the inline axis, filling the parent's width; the default when no orientation attribute is set. |
| `separator.vertical()` | Lays the rule along the block axis, stretching to fill the parent's height; requires a flex parent so the stretch can resolve. |

### Elements

A single root element. Children are optional; most separators are plain rules.

| Element | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `separator.root(attrs, children)` | The separator rule. Pass children to render centered content over the line. |

### Selectors

CSS selectors stamped on the separator's markup, available for overriding or layering app-specific styles.

| Selector | Matches |
| --- | --- |
| `[data-slot="separator"]` | The separator root. |
| `[data-orientation="horizontal\|vertical"]` | The root, tagged when an orientation attribute is applied. |
| `[data-content="true"]` | The root, tagged when centered content is present. |
| `[data-slot="separator-content"]` | The wrapper around centered content. |

## Accessibility

**Decorative by default.** Each separator carries a fixed role="none": the rule is a visual cue, not a semantic boundary, and assistive tech skips it while still reading any centered content. If a division between regions should be announced, render your own element with role="separator" and stamp data-slot="separator" on it to reuse the rule's styling.

